{"_id": "ahw1booz1ahYeip1","name": "Ranger","permission": {"default": 0},"type": "class","data": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a ranger, you gain the following class features.</p><h3>Hit Points</h3><p><strong>Hit Dice:</strong>&nbsp;[[/r 1d10]] per ranger level<br><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong>&nbsp;10 + your Constitution modifier<br><strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong>&nbsp;[[/r 1d10]] (or 6) + your Constitution modifier per ranger level after 1st</p><h3>Proficiencies</h3><p><strong>Armor:</strong>&nbsp;Light armor, medium armor, shields<br><strong>Weapons:</strong>&nbsp;Simple weapons, martial weapons<br><strong>Tools:</strong>&nbsp;None<br><strong>Saving Throws:</strong>&nbsp;Strength, Dexterity<br><strong>Skills:</strong>&nbsp;Choose three from Animal Handling, Athletics, Insight, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Stealth, and Survival</p><h3>Equipment</h3><p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p><ul><li>(a) scale mail or (b) leather armor</li><li>(a) two shortswords or (b) two simple melee weapons</li><li>(a) a dungeoneer’s pack or (b) an explorer’s pack</li><li>A longbow and a quiver of 20 arrows</li></ul><h4>Proficiencies</h4><p>Alternatively, you can ignore the equipment listed above and in your background, and buy [[/r 5d4 * 10]] gp worth of equipment from Chapter 5 of the Player’s Handbook.</p><h1>Ranger Advancement</h1><table><thead><tr><td>Level</td><td>Proficiency Bonus</td><td>Features</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1st</td><td>+2</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.iofeeH3xahh0naev]{Favored Enemy}, @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.ohsohfahrao8Hu5u]{Natural Explorer}</td></tr><tr><td>2nd</td><td>+2</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.sieghaeyu0nohDie]{Fighting Style (Ranger)}, @Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.u6xV3Ki3TXRrD7zg]{Spellcasting}</td></tr><tr><td>3rd</td><td>+2</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.bai8sueFaemah2mo]{Ranger Conclaves}, @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.aid9poetiyooceaF]{Primeval Awareness}</td></tr><tr><td>4th</td><td>+2</td><td>@Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.s0Cc2zcX0JzIgam5]{Ability Score Improvement}</td></tr><tr><td>5th</td><td>+3</td><td>2nd&nbsp;Level Spell Slot, Ranger Conclave feature</td></tr><tr><td>6th</td><td>+3</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.Ci1oe0eitae4ohsh]{Greater Favored Enemy}</td></tr><tr><td>7th</td><td>+3</td><td>Ranger Conclave feature</td></tr><tr><td>8th</td><td>+3</td><td>@Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.s0Cc2zcX0JzIgam5]{Ability Score Improvement}, @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.Keet3ohFe0ohNgei]{Fleet-Footed}</td></tr><tr><td>9th</td><td>+4</td><td>3rd&nbsp;Level Spell Slot</td></tr><tr><td>10th</td><td>+4</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.SijaiseecooDie6e]{Hide in Plain Sight}</td></tr><tr><td>11th</td><td>+4</td><td>Ranger Conclave feature</td></tr><tr><td>12th</td><td>+4</td><td>@Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.s0Cc2zcX0JzIgam5]{Ability Score Improvement}</td></tr><tr><td>13th</td><td>+5</td><td>4th&nbsp;Level Spell Slot</td></tr><tr><td>14th</td><td>+5</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.uaPieyae2taihiaK]{Vanish}</td></tr><tr><td>15th</td><td>+5</td><td>Ranger Conclave feature</td></tr><tr><td>16th</td><td>+5</td><td>@Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.s0Cc2zcX0JzIgam5]{Ability Score Improvement}</td></tr><tr><td>17th</td><td>+6</td><td>5th&nbsp;Level Spell Slot</td></tr><tr><td>18th</td><td>+6</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.xacoh5ohJeephoni]{Feral Senses}</td></tr><tr><td>19th</td><td>+6</td><td>@Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.s0Cc2zcX0JzIgam5]{Ability Score Improvement}</td></tr><tr><td>20th</td><td>+6</td><td>@Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.aekav0aes5chuV7u]{Foe Slayer}</td></tr></tbody></table><h1>Ranger Conclaves</h1><p>A classic expression of the ranger ideal is the Hunter.</p><h2>Hunter</h2><p>Some rangers seek to master weapons to better protect civilization from the terrors of the wilderness. Members of the Hunter Conclave learn specialized fighting techniques for use against the most dire threats, from rampaging ogres and hordes of orcs to towering giants and terrifying dragons.</p><h3>Hunter Features (NOT UPDATED FOR 5eUARevisedRanger)</h3><p>3rd Level: @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.wrxIW5sDfmGr3u5s]{Hunter's Prey}</p><p>5rd Level: @Compendium[dnd5e.classfeatures.XogoBnFWmCAHXppo]{Extra Attack}</p><p>7th Level: @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.WgQrqjmeyMqDzVt3]{Defensive Tactics}</p><p>11th Level: @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.7zlTRRXT1vWSBGjX]{Multiattack}</p><p>15th Level: @Compendium[5eUARevisedRanger.classfeatures.a0Sq88dgnREcIMfl]{Superior Hunter's Defense}</p>","chat": "","unidentified": ""},"source": "5eUARevisedRanger","levels": 1,"subclass": "","hitDice": "d10","hitDiceUsed": 0,"skills": {"number": 2,"choices": [],"value": []},"spellcasting": "half","damage": {"parts": []}},"flags": {"dynamiceffects": {"equipActive": false,"alwaysActive": false,"effects": []}},"img": "systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/green_04.jpg"}